        "resumo": "The macro question of the research proposal is to provide security computing on IoT devices in a home ecosystem, under the supervision from your Internet Service Provider (ISP). To this end, the ISP must have technical conditions to monitor the IoT device. However, the client of this ISP does not accept access to the device. afraid that the ISP will access the private and private data that the device IoT may contain. Between the two, client and ISP, there may be a possible attack due to, for example, to a vulnerability that is unknown to the customer and that the ISP can to fight. This dilemma between the parties is current and needs to be investigated to propose ways to access the IoT device by the ISP for the purposes of: – monitoring a possible attack, – vulnerability analysis and – mitigation in the event of a security breach that may compromise, in addition to the client's other IT and/or IoT equipment, the ISP IT infrastructure.",
