    {
        "titulo": "Terrestrial-Underwater Wireless Communication Networks with Self-Energized UAVs Utilizing THz/VLC for Enhanced Connectivity",
        "alunos": "Hanojhan Rajahrajasingh",
        "orientador": "Jayakody Arachchilage Dushantha Nalin Kumara, Marko Beko",
        "ano": "2025",
        "licenciatura": "Não encontrado",
        "email": "hanojhansingh@gmail.com",
        "resumo": "This research proposes a sustainable, high-speed communication framework using UAV-assisted hybrid Terahertz (THz) and Visible Light Communication (VLC) technologies for integrated terrestrial and underwater wireless networks. Leveraging UAVs as mobile relays, the system overcomes distance and attenuation constraints of THz and VLC links, ensuring robust connectivity across air, surface, and submerged environments. A novel dual-color OOK modulation scheme is introduced to enhance transmission efficiency, particularly for underwater VLC links where range and scattering pose unique challenges. The project further incorporates Simultaneous Lightwave Information and Power Transfer (SLIPT) and nonlinear energy harvesting models to enable autonomous UAV and surface relay operations. Performance will be evaluated through analytical modeling and simulation, focusing on BER, outage probability, and energy optimization. This work addresses pressing challenges in environmental monitoring, oceanic exploration, and emergency communications, contributing to the development of next-generation sustainable, self-powered, and high-data-rate communication systems.",
