        "resumo": "Cybersecurity threats are increasingly frequent and complex, yet the average user and even IT professionals often lack timely and accurate guidance during an incident. General-purpose chatbots powered by large language models (LLMs) offer impressive general knowledge capabilities but fall short in providing domain-specific, contextual, and trustworthy responses during security events. This thesis proposes the development of a conversational AI system, specialized in cybersecurity, capable of offering real-time, actionable responses based on a validated and dynamic knowledge base. The system will integrate retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), expert-curated playbooks, and contextual inference to assist users in detecting, understanding, and mitigating cyber threats.",
